## Scope

This file summarizes **[Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink)** as vendored in the repo’s **`ink/`** directory (reference clone — **do not edit**; see `docs/architecture.md`). It reflects the **`ink`** npm dependency version aligned with that tree (currently **7.x**).

Authoritative long-form docs: **`ink/readme.md`**. Public types and exports: **`ink/src/index.ts`** and built **`ink/build/`** after `npm run build` inside `ink/`.

## Mental model

- Ink is a **custom React renderer** for the terminal, not DOM. Normal **React** rules (hooks, state, effects) apply; layout uses **Yoga** (Flexbox-like props on **`Box`**).
- One **`render()`** call mounts a tree and drives stdout; **one live Ink instance per `stdout`** until **`unmount()`**.

## Install shape (for this repo)

- **`ink`** is the library; you also need **`react`** and, for TypeScript, **`@types/react`** (Ink’s peers: React **≥ 19.2** per upstream `package.json`).
- Upstream declares **`engines.node: ">=22"`** for the Ink package itself; **ink-cli-demo** runs on **Bun** — verify behavior; do not assume every Ink dev script works under Bun without checking.

## `render(element, options?)` → `Instance`

```tsx
import {render, Text} from 'ink';

const inst = render(<Text>Hi</Text>, {/* optional RenderOptions */});
// inst.rerender(<Text>Bye</Text>);
// inst.unmount();
// await inst.waitUntilExit();
```

**`Instance`** (from `render`): **`rerender`**, **`unmount`**, **`waitUntilExit()`** (promise settles on exit; resolves with value passed to **`exit()`** or rejects with passed **`Error`**), **`waitUntilRenderFlush()`**, **`cleanup()`**, **`clear()`**.

**Notable `RenderOptions`:** `stdout` / `stdin` / `stderr` streams; **`debug`** (append frames instead of replace); **`exitOnCtrlC`**; **`patchConsole`**; **`onRender`**; **`isScreenReaderEnabled`** (or `INK_SCREEN_READER=true`); **`maxFps`**; **`incrementalRendering`**; **`concurrent`** (React concurrent mode — affects timing, tests may need `act()`); **`kittyKeyboard`**; **`interactive`** (auto false in CI / non-TTY); **`alternateScreen`**.

**Caveat:** Calling **`render()`** again on the **same `stdout`** before **`unmount()`** is unsupported (Ink warns and reuses instance).

## `useApp()` — lifecycle

From **`useApp()`**: **`exit(errorOrResult?)`** — unmount; `exit()` → `waitUntilExit()` resolves `undefined`; `exit(err)` rejects; `exit(value)` resolves with `value`. Also **`waitUntilRenderFlush()`** after frames commit (see upstream JSDoc).

## Core components (from `ink`)

| Export | Role |
|--------|------|
| **`Text`** | Styled string output (e.g. `color`, `bold`); main leaf for text. |
| **`Box`** | Flex container (`flexDirection`, `justifyContent`, padding/margin, borders, etc.) — primary layout primitive. |
| **`Static`** | Append-only / “log” region; items typically `key`ed; useful for completed lines above a live UI. |
| **`Newline`**, **`Spacer`** | Layout helpers. |
| **`Transform`** | Wrap children to transform output per line. |

**Accessibility:** **`Box`** supports `aria-*` props when screen reader mode is on (see readme).

## Hooks (common)

| Hook | Use |
|------|-----|
| **`useInput`** | Keyboard input handler; receives input string and **`Key`** metadata (arrows, ctrl, meta, kitty extras when enabled). |
| **`usePaste`** | Bracketed paste / paste events. |
| **`useStdin` / `useStdout` / `useStderr`** | Access streams and TTY metadata (`isTTY`, etc.). |
| **`useFocus` / `useFocusManager`** | Focus order for interactive widgets. |
| **`useCursor`** | Show/hide terminal cursor. |
| **`useWindowSize`** | Terminal columns/rows. |
| **`useBoxMetrics`** | Measure layout box for a ref. |
| **`useAnimation`** | Time-based animation helper. |
| **`useIsScreenReaderEnabled`** | Whether a11y mode is active. |

## `renderToString(element, {columns?})`

Synchronous string output **without** a terminal session. **`useInput`**, **`useStdin`**, **`useStdout`**, **`useStderr`**, **`useApp`**, **`useFocus`**, **`useFocusManager`** are **no-ops** (do not throw). **`useEffect`** state updates do **not** affect returned string; **`useLayoutEffect`** updates **do**. **`<Static>`** output is prepended to dynamic output. Throws propagate after cleanup.

## Other exports

- **`measureElement`** — measure a laid-out element.
- **`kittyFlags`**, **`kittyModifiers`**, types from **`kitty-keyboard`** — Kitty keyboard protocol helpers.

## Testing and devtools

- Component tests: community **`ink-testing-library`** (`lastFrame()`, etc.) — see **`ink/readme.md` § Testing**.
- React DevTools: optional **`react-devtools-core`**, run with **`DEV=true`**, see readme § Using React Devtools.

## When to open `./ink` source

Use **`ink/readme.md`** for props tables, recipes, and edge cases. Open **`ink/src/components/*`** or **`ink/src/hooks/*`** when you need exact prop types or hook option shapes beyond this cheat sheet.
